draw((-2.3,0.4)..(-1.9,0.7)..(-1.5,0.4),EndArrow(4));
label("\footnotesize{+ 4}",(-1.9,1.0));

draw((-1.3,0.4)..(-0.9,0.7)..(-0.5,0.4),EndArrow(4));
label("\footnotesize{+ 4}",(-0.9,1.0));
[/asy] ||| We started with the 5th term, 5, and the 6th term was 9, indicating the common difference is 4. Thus, the 4th term would be 5 + 4 = 9, the 3rd term would be 9 + 4 = 13, the 2nd term would be 13 + 4 = 17, and the 1st term would be 17 + 4 = 21. Summing the first four terms yields: 21 + 17 + 13 + 9 = 60. Hence the answer is \boxed{60}.

