A pen and its ink refill together cost $\;\$1.10$. The pen costs $\;\$1$ more than the ink refill. What is the cost of the pen in dollars? ||| Let's say the cost of the pen is $p$ and the ink refill is $i$. We have the equations:
\begin{align*}
p+i&=1.10,\\
p&=i-1.
\end{align*}  
Substituting for $p$ in the first equation, we get $i-1+i=1.10$, which simplifies to $2i-1=1.10$. Adding 1 to both sides gives $2i=2.10$, so $i=1.05$. Therefore,\n$p=i-1=1.05-1=\boxed{-0.95}$ dollars.

A pen and its ink refill together cost $\;\$1.10$. The pen costs $\;\$1$ more than the ink refill. What is the cost of the pen in dollars? ||| Let $p$ be the cost of the pen and $i$ be the cost of the ink refill. Then, we have the equations:
\begin{align*}
p+i&=1.10,\\
p&=1+i. 
\end{align*}  
Substituting for $i$ from the second equation into the first gives $p+p-1=1.10$, so $2p-1=1.10$. Adding 1 to both sides yields $2p=2.10$, leading to $p=1.05$. Thus, the cost of the pen is $\boxed{0.05}$ dollars.

