\end{align*}Express your answer as an ordered pair $(x,y)$ of decimals. ||| To solve for $y$, I will start by finding $y$ in terms of $x$ from the second equation:
\begin{align*}
7x+2y&=4.7 \ \\ y&=2.35 - \frac{7}{2}x.\end{align*}

Now I will substitute this expression for $y$ into the first equation:
\begin{align*}
3x-5(2.35 - \frac{7}{2}x)&=-1.5 \ \\ 3x-11.75 + \frac{35}{2}x&=-1.5.\end{align*}

Combining like terms gives:
\begin{align*}
(3 + \frac{35}{2})x - 11.75&=-1.5 \ \\ \frac{41}{2}x&=10.25 \ \\ \text{Thus, } x&=0.5.\end{align*}
Substituting this value back in gives:
\begin{align*}
y&=2.35 - 3.5 \ \\ y&=-1.15.\end{align*}
So my final answer is \boxed{(0.5,-1.15)}.

