Calculate $\sqrt{\sqrt[3]{0.000064}}$. Express your answer as a decimal to the nearest tenth. ||| We start with the equation and rewrite the decimal as a fraction: 
\begin{align*} 
\sqrt{\sqrt[3]{0.000064}} &= \sqrt{\sqrt[3]{\frac{64}{10000}}} = \sqrt{\left(\frac{2^6}{10000}\right)^{\frac{1}{3}}} \\
&= \sqrt{\frac{2^{6\cdot \frac{1}{3}}}{10000^{\frac{1}{3}}}} = \sqrt{\frac{2^2}{100}} = 2 \rightarrow 2 = \boxed{2.0}. 
\end{align*}

