label("$R$",(-2,0),SE);
[/asy]What is the area of $\triangle PQR?$ ||| The slope of line segment $QP$ is $1$. Starting from point $P(1,6)$, we move 6 units to the left and 6 units down to find point $Q$. So, $Q$ must be at $(-5,0)$. \n\nThe slope of line segment $RP$ is $2$. The rise from $P$ is $6$ units, but I think the run should be $2$ units, since $P$ is higher than $R$. So, point $R$ should be $(-1,4)$. \n\nUsing these coordinates, the distance $QR = -1 - (-5) = 4$. The height from $P$ to the $x$-axis is still 6 units. The area of triangle $PQR$ can then be calculated as $$\frac{1}{2} \cdot 4 \cdot 6 = \boxed{12}.$$

