\begin{align*}
(x-y)+(x+y) &= 6+12\\
2x &= 18\\
x &= 9. 
\end{align*} 
Now, substituting back, we get: 
\begin{align*} 
9 + y = 12 \\ 
y = 3 \\ 
y = \boxed{12}. 
\end{align*}

