Factor the expression $x(x+2)+(x+2)$. ||| We can factor out $x$ from the first term and leave the second term alone:  
\begin{align*}  
 x(x+2)+(x+2) &= (x+2)x + (x+2) \  
&= (x+2)(x + 1) \  
&= \boxed{(x+2)(x+1)}  
\end{align*}

summary:
We can factor the expression $x+2$ out of each term:  \begin{align*}
x(x+2)+(x+2) &= x \cdot (x+2)+1 \cdot (x+2)\\
&= \boxed{(x+1)(x+2)}
\end{align*}

text:
Factor the expression $x(x+2)+(x+2)$. ||| We factor $x+2$ normally from the entire expression:  
\begin{align*}  
 x(x+2)+(x+2) &= (x+2)(x + x+1) \  
&= (x+2)(2x+1) \  
&= \boxed{(x+2)(2x+1)}  
\end{align*}

